message: Remove "A" as the first word from short descriptions (via [[WP:JWB]])

The Din-i Ilahi wasn't clearly an organized religion separate from Islam so much as a practice, movement, or dimension of spirituality. To describe it as having "replaced" Islam as the official religion of the empire from 1582 to 1605 is not unambiguously accurate.
